{"name":"Mathlib.NumberTheory.LegendreSymbol.GaussSum","instances":[],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.NumberTheory.LegendreSymbol.AddCharacter","Mathlib.NumberTheory.LegendreSymbol.ZModChar","Mathlib.Algebra.CharP.CharAndCard"],"declarations":[{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/NumberTheory/LegendreSymbol/GaussSum.lean#L268-L370","name":"FiniteField.two_pow_card","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/LegendreSymbol/GaussSum.html#FiniteField.two_pow_card","doc":"For every finite field `F` of odd characteristic, we have `2^(#F/2) = χ₈(#F)` in `F`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/NumberTheory/LegendreSymbol/GaussSum.lean#L215-L241","name":"Char.card_pow_card","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/LegendreSymbol/GaussSum.html#Char.card_pow_card","doc":"When `F` and `F'` are finite fields and `χ : F → F'` is a nontrivial quadratic character,\nthen `(χ(-1) * #F)^(#F'/2) = χ(#F')`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/NumberTheory/LegendreSymbol/GaussSum.lean#L200-L210","name":"Char.card_pow_char_pow","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/LegendreSymbol/GaussSum.html#Char.card_pow_char_pow","doc":"If the square of the Gauss sum of a quadratic character is `χ(-1) * #R`,\nthen we get, for all `n : ℕ`, the relation `(χ(-1) * #R) ^ (p^n/2) = χ(p^n)`,\nwhere `p` is the (odd) characteristic of the target ring `R'`.\nThis version can be used when `R` is not a field, e.g., `ℤ/8ℤ`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/NumberTheory/LegendreSymbol/GaussSum.lean#L177-L182","name":"MulChar.IsQuadratic.gaussSum_frob_iter","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/LegendreSymbol/GaussSum.html#MulChar.IsQuadratic.gaussSum_frob_iter","doc":"For a quadratic character `χ` and when the characteristic `p` of the target ring\nis a unit in the source ring and `n` is a natural number, the `p^n`th power of the Gauss\nsum of`χ` and `ψ` is `χ (p^n)` times the original Gauss sum. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/NumberTheory/LegendreSymbol/GaussSum.lean#L167-L171","name":"MulChar.IsQuadratic.gaussSum_frob","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/LegendreSymbol/GaussSum.html#MulChar.IsQuadratic.gaussSum_frob","doc":"For a quadratic character `χ` and when the characteristic `p` of the target ring\nis a unit in the source ring, the `p`th power of the Gauss sum of`χ` and `ψ` is\n`χ p` times the original Gauss sum. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/NumberTheory/LegendreSymbol/GaussSum.lean#L156-L160","name":"gaussSum_frob","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/LegendreSymbol/GaussSum.html#gaussSum_frob","doc":"When `R'` has prime characteristic `p`, then the `p`th power of the Gauss sum\nof `χ` and `ψ` is the Gauss sum of `χ^p` and `ψ^p`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/NumberTheory/LegendreSymbol/GaussSum.lean#L132-L137","name":"gaussSum_sq","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/LegendreSymbol/GaussSum.html#gaussSum_sq","doc":"When `χ` is a nontrivial quadratic character, then the square of `gaussSum χ ψ`\nis `χ(-1)` times the cardinality of `R`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/NumberTheory/LegendreSymbol/GaussSum.lean#L113-L127","name":"gaussSum_mul_gaussSum_eq_card","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/LegendreSymbol/GaussSum.html#gaussSum_mul_gaussSum_eq_card","doc":"We have `gaussSum χ ψ * gaussSum χ⁻¹ ψ⁻¹ = Fintype.card R`\nwhen `χ` is nontrivial and `ψ` is primitive (and `R` is a field). "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/NumberTheory/LegendreSymbol/GaussSum.lean#L79-L83","name":"gaussSum_mulShift","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/LegendreSymbol/GaussSum.html#gaussSum_mulShift","doc":"Replacing `ψ` by `mulShift ψ a` and multiplying the Gauss sum by `χ a` does not change it. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/NumberTheory/LegendreSymbol/GaussSum.lean#L74-L75","name":"gaussSum","kind":"def","docLink":"./Mathlib/NumberTheory/LegendreSymbol/GaussSum.html#gaussSum","doc":"Definition of the Gauss sum associated to a multiplicative and an additive character. "}]}